      • loadCustomExporters

        public static void loadCustomExporters()
        If the config setting "exporter.enable_custom_exporters" is enabled, load classes implementing the PatientExporter or PostCompletionExporter interfaces from the classpath, via the ServiceLoader.

      • loadCodeMappers

        public static void loadCodeMappers()
        Load any configured code mappers. Code mappers are configured via the synthea.properties file and a sample configuration is shown below: 
         exporter.code_map.icd_10=export/anti_amyloid_code_map.json
 exporter.code_map.cpt=export/phlebotomy_code_map.json,export/neurology_code_map.json
        The above define a single code map for ICD-10 codes and two code maps for CPT codes.

      • filterForExport

        public static Person filterForExport​(Person original,
                                     int yearsToKeep,
                                     long endTime)
        Filter the patient's history to only the last __ years but also include relevant history from before that. Exclude any history that occurs after the specified end_time -- typically this is the current time/System.currentTimeMillis().
        Parameters:
        original - The Person to filter.
        yearsToKeep - The last __ years to keep.
        endTime - The time the history ends.
        Returns:
        Modified Person with history expunged.

      • getOutputFolder

        public static java.io.File getOutputFolder​(java.lang.String folderName,
                                           Person person)
        Get the folder where the patient record should be stored. See the configuration settings "exporter.subfolders_by_id_substring" and "exporter.baseDirectory".
        Parameters:
        folderName - The base folder to use.
        person - The person being exported.
        Returns:
        Either the base folder provided, or a subdirectory, depending on configuration settings.

      • filename

        public static java.lang.String filename​(Person person,
                                        java.lang.String tag,
                                        java.lang.String extension)
        Get the filename to used to export the patient record. See the configuration setting "exporter.use_uuid_filenames".
        Parameters:
        person - The person being exported.
        tag - A tag to add to the filename before the extension.
        extension - The file extension to use.
        Returns:
        The filename only (not a path).
